message: "If you use Perception-First Design in your work, please cite it."
title: "Perception-First Design"
version: "3.4"
date-released: "2026-03-04"
license: "CC-BY-SA-4.0"
type: "dataset"
authors:
  - family-names: "Kovalik"
    given-names: "Stefan"
    affiliation: "Aurochs"
    website: "https://aurochs.agency"
repository-code: "https://github.com/skovalik/perception-first-design"
url: "https://aurochs.agency/perception-first-design/"
abstract: >
  A five-layer web design methodology grounded in cognitive psychology. Applies
  predictive processing, cognitive load theory, processing fluency, perception
  bias optimization, and decision architecture to how people perceive, process,
  and decide. 77 peer-reviewed citations from 3 non-overlapping literatures.
  15 years of applied practice. Includes a Claude Code plugin for automated
  evaluation and a YAML heuristic rule corpus.
keywords:
  - perception-first-design
  - cognitive-psychology
  - web-design
  - ux
  - processing-fluency
  - decision-architecture
  - design-methodology
  - neurodivergent-design
  - adhd
  - cognitive-load
